<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06040b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06040b">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06040b"> 40(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> coq repond pas / apr&egrave;s il a &eacute;t&eacute; mort / eat dead fox with spoon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Paul, &agrave; cinq ans et demi, apr&egrave;s avoir entendu dire par sa sour la fable de La Fontaine, <cite>le Coq et le Renard</cite>, imagina aussit&ocirc;t l&apos;histoire suivante: &ldquo;Il y avait une fois un coq...il &eacute;tait sur un mur...ce coq &eacute;tait en fer...il &eacute;tait gros comme un coq v&eacute;ritable...il avait le bec ouvert...Un renard pass, puis il lui parle...le coq r&eacute;pond pas...il l&apos;appelle, <mark>le coq r&eacute;pond pas</mark> ... le renard saute sur le mur...puis il mord le coq...le coq &eacute;tait en fer, il &eacute;tait dur...il en mange un morceau, &ccedil;a lui perce les boyaux...puis <mark>apr&egrave;s il a &eacute;t&eacute; mort</mark>...les chiens viennent, puis ils l&apos;emportent et le mangent &hellip;. <font color="green">[Paul, at five-and-a-half years old, after having heard the fable of La Fontaine, the Rooster and the Fox, by his sister, immediately imagined the following story: &ldquo;There was once a rooster ... he was on a wall ... this rooster was iron ... he was as big as a real rooster ... he had the beak open ... A fox pass, then he speaks to him ... the rooster does not answer ... he the call, the cock does not answer ... the fox jumps on the wall ... then he bites the cock ... the cock was iron, it was hard ... he eats a piece, it pierces the bowels. ..then after he was dead ... the dogs come, then they take it away and eat it&rdquo;]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 19</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01110b" href="c01all.htm#c01110b">VI.C.01:110(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
